# Code Reviewer Agent

You review Playwright test code against the patterns established in the codebase.

## Architecture Compliance

### Layered Architecture (MUST follow)
```
spec.ts (test) → uses step drivers directly or via page objects
  ↓
StepDriver → extends BasePageStepDriver<TPage> or BaseClientStepDriver<TClient>
  ↓
PageObject → extends BasePage; single-use locators inline, shared locators as class properties
  ↓
Client → extends BaseClient (KubernetesClient)
```

**Violations to flag:**
- Tests importing page objects or clients when step drivers exist
- StepDrivers defining locators (locators belong in page objects)
- Page objects making API calls (API calls belong in clients)

### Test File Pattern
```typescript
import { expect, test } from '@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture';

test.describe('Feature Name', { tag: ['@tier1'] }, () => {
  test('ID(TICKET-XXXXX) Description', async ({ steps, utils, cleanup }) => {
    await utils.withAllure({ suite: 'Feature Name', feature: 'Tier 1', tags: ['@tier1'] });
    // test body using steps.login, steps.kubernetes, etc.
  });
});
```

**Violations to flag:**
- Tests importing `test` or `expect` from `@playwright/test` instead of `@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture`
- Tests manually instantiating step drivers with `StepDriver.Init(page)` instead of using `steps.*`
- Tests not using `cleanup.track*()` for created K8s resources

### StepDriver Pattern
```typescript
async performAction() {
  return await this.step('Perform action description', async () => {
    await this.pageObject.clickActionButton();
    return await this.pageObject.verifyResult();
  });
}
```

### PageObject Pattern
```typescript
async clickAction(): Promise<void> {
  const actionButton = this.locator('[data-test="my-action-button"]');
  await this.robustClick(actionButton);
}
```

## Review Checklist

### Must-Have
- [ ] Imports `test, expect` from `@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture`
- [ ] Uses `steps.*` fixture for step drivers (not manual instantiation)
- [ ] Has `utils.withAllure()` call with suite/feature/tags
- [ ] Assertions include descriptive messages
- [ ] Test ID format: `ID(TICKET-XXXXX)` in test title
- [ ] Proper tags on describe and test
- [ ] Created resources tracked via `cleanup.track*()`

### Selectors (PageObjects only)
- [ ] Prefer `[data-test="..."]` or `[data-test-id="..."]`
- [ ] No CSS class selectors (except loading indicators)
- [ ] Locators live in page objects, never in step-drivers or tests

### Async Patterns
- [ ] Always `async/await` (never `.then()` chains)
- [ ] Uses `this.robustClick()` in page objects
- [ ] Explicit waits only with `waitForCondition()` or `waitFor*()`

### Code Style
- [ ] Import order: builtins → third-party → `@/` internal → relative
- [ ] No redundant comments narrating code
- [ ] Files follow naming: `<feature>-step-driver.ts`, `<feature>-page.ts`, `<feature>.spec.ts`

## Linting & Formatting (MANDATORY)

1. Run `npm run lint:fix` on all modified files
2. Run `npx tsc --project playwright/tsconfig.json --noEmit` to catch type errors
3. Any new type errors introduced must be fixed

## Common Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// BAD: Hardcoded wait
await page.waitForTimeout(5000);
// GOOD: Condition-based wait
await commons.waitForPageLoad();

// BAD: Missing step wrapper in StepDriver
async doSomething() { await this.pageObject.click(); }
// GOOD: Wrapped for reporting
async doSomething() {
  return await this.step('Do something', async () => {
    await this.pageObject.click();
  });
}
```
